Trade and Industry Minister Ebrahim Patel says under level four lockdown, restaurants will be able to deliver food to customers. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Trade and Industry Minister Ebrahim Patel says under level four lockdown, restaurants will be able to deliver food to customers. However, there will be no sit-down meals and no takeaway facilities at restaurants. READ: Smokers ready for a puff Government has warned that sticking to the regulations is key to ending the current lockdown. From 1 May, South Africa moves from level five to level four of the lockdown.